Bruce 11 May 2005
    - Eliminate some annoying 'undefined index' errors in PHP log. Note
      that in general the right way to use _GET[] is like this:
          $x=default_value;
          if (isset($_GET["x"])) $x=$_GET["x"];
      This prevents PHP notice-type error messages.
