David  25 July 2005
    - API: in start_worker_thread(), use pthread_sigmask()
        instead of sigprocmask() to block SIGALRM in the graphics thread.
        On Mac OS X, sigprocmask() blocks SIGALRM in all threads,
        which is not the intent.
        (From Bruce Allen)

    api/
        graphics_impl.C


